The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index fell 0.1 percent to 4,243.44. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index retreated 1 percent to 2,411.05.  SACI Falabella (FALAB)   retreated 0.3 percent to 4,213.1
pesos. The retailer pledged it would reduce imports for its
Argentinean stores, Clarin reported yesterday.  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK)  (SK CC) rose 0.9 percent to 930 pesos. The
Chilean industrial holding company acquired a stake in mining
services firm Godelius, the company said in an e-mailed
statement.  Sonda SA (SONDA)   rose 0.2 percent to 1,292 pesos, its
second day of gains. Chileâ€™s largest information technology and
software services company reported a 21 percent increase in
annual profit to 40.6 billion pesos ($82 million). The brokerage
units of Banco de Chile and Banco de Credito & Inversiones said
the results were above expectations.  To contact the reporter on this story:
